results.name: a(n) = A064097(n) - A003313(n).
comment: The positions where k = 0, 1, 2, ... occur for the first time are 1, 23, 129, 517, 2049, 4613, 33097, 33793, ... factorized as: 1, 23, 3*43, 11*47, 3*683, 7*659, 23*1439, 47*719, ... - _Antti Karttunen_, Aug 18 2017
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000 (also based on the b-file of A003313)
formula: It seems that sum(k = 1, n, a(k)) * log(n)/n^2 -> c (0.006 < c < 0.01).
